    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>April 19<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi>. 1850</date>.</p>
            <p>To the <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>;</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Reverend Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your communication of the <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst.
                conveying the<lb/> MS. Of <persName>Mr. Peynado</persName>, in reply to the Address
                to the Jews by the Synod of<lb/>
                <placeName>New York</placeName>, was duly received.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The copy of the “Occident,” for <date>January</date>, containing<lb/>
                <persName>Dr. Schlessinger's</persName> article, came to hand, several months ago.
                But<lb/> I only now learn, through your note, for the first time, to whom<lb/> I am
                indebted for that courtesy.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As the Address to which these replies are made,<lb/> emanated from
                the <hi rend="underline">Synod</hi>, it does not become the persons whose<lb/>
                signatures are affixed to it, merely as authenticating officers, to<lb/> speak for
                that body, in advance, or on its behalf, without authority.<lb/> The documents
                received from you, and any others on the same<lb/> subject, that may be received
                from any quarter, will be laid<lb/> before the Synod, at its next annual meeting in
                    <date>October</date>,—when,<lb/> I have no doubt, it will be as gratifying to
                the body, as it is to<lb/> myself, to welcome these notices of the address in
                question, and<lb/> to exhibit to the children of <persName>Abraham</persName>, its
                views on the points<lb/> submitted on the behalf of your people.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">With great respect,</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">your obedt. Servt.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">John M. Krebs</persName>, Stated Clerk</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">of the Synod of <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
